gui.morphspellpack:charm_lich_tome.title=Ritual of the Lich
gui.morphspellpack:charm_lich_tome.desc=Liches are formidable undead beings, created when a wizard seals their soul within a Soul Phylactery by immolating their body. This transformation is irreversible. To perform the ritual, a wizard must hold this tome, equip an empty phylactery, and construct an altar using 9 Soul Sands and 4 skulls positioned at the corners, facing inward. Light a fire at the center of the altar with the skulls directed towards it. The wizard must remain in the fire until the phylactery is fully charged. As a Lich, one cannot eat and must sustain themselves by consuming Soul Phylacteries. It is essential for a Lich to always wear their phylactery, or they will be greatly weakened. If a phylactery is destroyed, the Lich can perform the ritual again to create a new one.
gui.morphspellpack:charm_lich_tome_2.title=Vinculum Animae, Vol. I
gui.morphspellpack:charm_lich_tome_2.desc=The Lich Soul Receptacle, a vital artefact detailed herein, shelters the Lich's Soul Phylactery, ensuring its preservation. Upon succumbing to fatal blows, the Lich revives at this sanctum immediately, embracing undying persistence. The receptacle offers refuge to the phylactery, shielding it from harm and loss. Further empowerment is found by layering a magical crystal pyramid under the receptacle. Each layer, with the smallest starting at 3x3 block size, must be made of single elemental crystal block, augments its power. Up to 4 layers can be constructed this way, and each element can have a different effect, depending on its layer, starting from the smallest. The layers can belong to different elements. The effects of the crystal layers are tied to the fullness of the phylactery (25%% is required per layer).
gui.morphspellpack:charm_lich_tome_3.title=Vinculum Animae, Vol. II
gui.morphspellpack:charm_lich_tome_3.desc=The potent effects of the Lich's Soul Receptacle, when augmented by Elemental Crystals, are enumerated hereafter for each layer: I.: 10%% spell potency for the layer's element. II.: Magic: Passive mana regeneration; Other elements: During every lunar cycle, the receptacle grants the lich an unknown spell book of the crystal's element (starting from lower tiers). III.: Magic: Prevents players within 100 blocks from casting; Other elements: Spells of the crystal's element gain up to +2 for all spell modifiers, based on the distance from the receptacle (max 600 blocks) IV.: Magic: Empowerment; Fire: Fire Resistance; Ice: Frostbite Resistance; Lightning: Static Aura; Earth: Resistance, Necromancy: Wither effect immunity; Healing: Protection from sunburn; Sorcery: Using the Transportation spell with a Sorcery Wand on the receptacle always teleports you to your latest "death" point.
